1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE BILL 4299 By: Blair
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to memorial roads and bridges;
designating the Toby Keith Memorial Interchange;
8 directing markers be placed; providing for
codification; and providing an effective date.
9
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1698.501 of Title 69, unless
15 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 The interchange of Interstate 35 and Indian Hills Road in
17 Cleveland County shall be designated as the "Toby Keith Memorial
18 Interchange". The Department of Transportation shall cause suitable
19 markers bearing that name to be placed at the interchange.
20 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
